"title": "8765: grudge",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8765: grudge",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A persistent feeling of ill will or resentment held by one person against another, often as the result of an injury or insult. Christians are not to bear grudges against others; instead they are to forgive those who have wronged them.</p>\n<h2>Examples of those who held grudges</h2>\n<h3>Esau against Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:41\">GEN 27:41</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Joseph's brothers and Joseph</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:4\">GEN 37:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:5\">GEN 37:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:8\">GEN 37:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:18-Gen37:19\">GEN 37:18–37:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:23-Gen37:24\">GEN 37:23–37:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:15\">GEN 50:15</a></p>\n<h3>The Israelites against Moses and Aaron</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:1\">NUM 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:1-Num14:4\">NUM 14:1–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:27\">NUM 14:27</a></p>\n<h3>Saul against David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:7-1Sam18:9\">1SA 18:7–18:9</a></p>\n<h3>Ahab against Elijah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:16-1Kgs18:17\">1KI 18:16–18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:20\">1KI 21:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:8\">1KI 22:8</a></p>\n<h3>Herodias against John the Baptist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:18-Mark6:19\">MRK 6:18–6:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The disciples against others</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:6-Matt26:9\">MAT 26:6–26:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3-Mark14:5\">MRK 14:3–14:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:3-John12:6\">JHN 12:3–12:6</a></p>\n<h3>The Sadducees against the apostles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:17\">ACT 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>The Jews against Stephen</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:54\">ACT 7:54</a></p>\n<h2>Severe grudges that led to hatred and murder</h2>\n<h3>That of Abel by Cain</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:4-Gen4:8\">GEN 4:4–4:8</a></p>\n<h3>That of Joseph by his brothers, averted by Reuben</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:18-Gen37:20\">GEN 37:18–37:20</a></p>\n<h3>That of Amnon, on the orders of Absalom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:22\">2SA 13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:28-2Sam13:32\">2SA 13:28–13:32</a></p>\n<h3>That of John the Baptist by Herodias</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:22-Mark6:24\">MRK 6:22–6:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:27-Mark6:28\">MRK 6:27–6:28</a></p>\n<h2>Warnings against the holding of grudges</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:18\">LEV 19:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:10\">DEU 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:1-Judg8:3\">JDG 8:1–8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:2\">JOB 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:13\">JOB 36:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:11\">PRO 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:22\">PRO 20:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:17\">PRO 23:17</a></p>\n<h3>In Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:21-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:21–7:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:19-Matt15:20\">MAT 15:19–15:20</a></p>\n<h3>In the apostles' teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:17-Rom12:21\">ROM 12:17–12:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:15\">1TH 5:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:15\">GAL 5:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19-Gal5:21\">GAL 5:19–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:13-Phil2:15\">PHP 2:13–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:8\">COL 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24\">2TI 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:16\">JAS 3:14–3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:1\">1PE 2:1</a></p>\n<h2>Christians should not hold grudges</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:43-Matt5:47\">MAT 5:43–5:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a></p>",
